<H1><FONT color="#000000" face="mv boli"><B><center>INDIAN HERITAGE</center></B></FONT></H1>


<hr/>
<P>
    Indian heritage refers to the rich and vibrant culture, traditions, and historical achievements of India, spanning millennia and including diverse elements like architecture (e.g., Taj Mahal, Ajanta Caves), dance, music, literature, religions (Hinduism, Buddhism, Jainism, Sikhism), languages, and philosophical traditions. It is a treasure trove of UNESCO World Heritage Sites that reflect its continuous cultural traditions and significant contributions to global civilization.


<p align="right">Examples of Indian Heritage Sites
Cultural Sites: Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, Ajanta and Ellora Caves, Khajuraho, Hampi, and the Hill Forts of Rajasthan.
Natural Sites: Manas Wildlife Sanctuary and Keibul Lamjao National Park.
Mixed Sites: The Kanchenjunga National Park. </p>
<p align="left">Cultural Diversity:
India's heritage is characterized by its immense diversity in languages, festivals, performing arts, food, dance, and music, with regional variations across the subcontinent. </p>
